(1750, 1, '2015-04-20 02:06:57', '2015-04-20 02:06:57', '<h2>Objective</h2>\nI wanted to see if I could build a javascript function that would randomly generate an RGBA value that I could then assign to different elements in the DOM.\n<h2>Implementation</h2>\nI figured out that I needed to assign each RGB a random number between 0-255 and then concatenate them so it could be pushed into the CSS:\n<pre><code>var app = {\ncolorMachine: function() { \nvar R = getRandomInt(0, 255); \nvar G = getRandomInt(0, 255);\nvar B = getRandomInt(0, 255);\nvar randomColor = (R + "," + G + "," + B + "," + 1);\nvar newColor = "rgba(" + randomColor + ")";\nreturn newColor;\n},</code></pre>\nThen I used jQuery to assign the five background columns the color values, and set them to change at a random interval between 0.5 and 2 seconds:\n<pre><code>timeMachine:function(){\nvar T = getRandomInt(5, 20); \nvar newT = (T+"00");\nreturn newT;},\npageStyles: function(){ \n$("div #1 h1").html(app.colorMachine());\n$("div #1").css({ ''background-color'': app.colorMachine() });</code></pre>\n<h2>Next steps</h2>\nIt works pretty well now, but I want to make it more modular. Right now it needs to hook into div #ID''s to work, but I''d like to get it to the point where you could choose the number of columns and the code would automatically create them.', 'Javascript random color experiment', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1722-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-04-20 02:06:57', '2015-04-20 02:06:57', '', 1722, 'http://localhost/fn/1722-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1751, 1, '2015-03-26 03:38:12', '2015-03-26 03:38:12', 'I came to coding and Web development almost by accident: In my final semester of undergrad a beginning HTML was the only class that fit my schedule. I took to it immediately. It was like playing with Legos again: write the code and see the result!\r\n\r\nAfter graduation I continued to tinker with HTML and CSS, but I decided to take it seriously after getting laid off from a job I wasn''t passionate about in the summer of 2012.\r\n\r\nMy time in the IDM program has been transformative for me. I''m much more advanced in design and coding, and I have a more rounded skillset that includes UX design, project management and marketing.\r\n\r\nAnd the transformation wasn''t just in education. Here''s a list of things that happened in my life since I started the IDM program:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up green"></i> Got a job</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-thumbs-o-down red"></i> Moved</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up green"></i> Got a better job</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up green "></i> Got married</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up green"></i> Became a father</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-thumbs-o-down red"></i> Moved again</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up green"></i> Got promoted</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nGoing forward I want to pursue becoming a front-end developer. I''m passionate about writing efficient, semantic code and expanding my knowledge to new tools and languages.', 'About', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about', '', '', '2015-03-26 03:39:20', '2015-03-26 03:39:20', '', 0, 'http://localhost/fn/?post_type=project&#038;p=1751', 0, 'project', '', 0),
